# 2. Information We Collect

Lensiary only collects information necessary to provide the features you choose to use.

Depending on your use of the App, you may choose to provide:

- Contact lens prescriptions
- Lens brand and product information
- Lens inventory
- Lens insertion and removal times
- Lens wear history
- Comfort, irritation and symptom logs
- Personal notes
- App preferences and settings

When you choose to log certain events, Lensiary may also request access to your location in order to retrieve local environmental conditions from Apple's WeatherKit service.

These environmental conditions may include:

- Temperature
- Humidity
- Air Quality
- Other weather conditions made available by Apple WeatherKit

The environmental information is stored alongside the event to help you identify patterns between your contact lens comfort and your surroundings.

---

# 3. How Your Information Is Stored

Lensiary is designed so that your information remains under your control.

Your contact lens information, wear history and logged events are stored locally on your Apple device using Apple's secure storage technologies.

If you enable iCloud synchronisation, your information may also be securely synchronised through your personal Apple account using Apple's CloudKit infrastructure.

The developer does not have access to your personal data stored on your device or within your personal iCloud account.

---

# 4. Apple Intelligence

Lensiary may make use of Apple Intelligence features to provide helpful insights, predictions and summaries.

Where supported by Apple, these features operate on your device whenever possible.

Lensiary does not use Apple Intelligence to profile users or share personal information with the developer.

---

# 5. Siri and App Intents

Lensiary supports Siri and App Intents to allow hands-free interaction with the App.

When you choose to use Siri, your requests are processed by Apple in accordance with Apple's own Privacy Policy.

The developer does not receive recordings of your voice commands.

---

# 6. Location Information

Lensiary requests access to your location only when you choose to log specific events, such as:

- Inserting contact lenses
- Removing contact lenses
- Recording comfort or irritation

Your location is used solely to retrieve local environmental conditions from Apple's WeatherKit service.

Lensiary does **not** use your location to:

- Track your movements
- Build a history of your locations
- Share your location with third parties
- Deliver advertising
- Sell location information

Lensiary stores the environmental conditions associated with the event. The App is designed to minimise retention of precise location information wherever possible.

Location access is optional and can be disabled at any time in iOS Settings. The App will continue to function normally without location access, although environmental conditions will not be recorded.

---

# 7. Camera and Photos

If you choose to scan contact lens packaging or attach photographs, Lensiary will request permission to access your camera or photo library.

These images are used only for the features you request.

---

# 8. Notifications

If enabled, Lensiary may send notifications relating to:

- Lens replacement reminders
- Wear duration reminders
- Inventory reminders
- Other reminders you configure

Notification permissions may be changed at any time in iOS Settings.

---

# 9. Health Information

Lensiary allows you to record information relating to your contact lens use and comfort.

Lensiary is **not** a medical device.

The App does **not** provide medical advice, diagnosis or treatment.

Any health-related information you record is intended solely to help you manage your contact lens usage and identify personal trends.

Always consult a qualified eye care professional regarding medical concerns.

